@NODE Introduction "Picture Overview: Introduction"


What is it?@{uu}@{ub}

PictureOverview ist a program to make an overview of pictures of a directory.
Its like PhotoFolio but much faster. Some Functions are not inbuild but i dont know for what they
are anyway. 
PhotoFolio was a great Programm, the best what i could find, but it crashes with some special
Files in the Dirs, with too many pictures open very slow sorting, has problems with
WarpOS - display errors sometimes crashes and a not optimal represantation.
Because of that i wrote PhotoOverview.
 

Features:
-More then twice fast loading compared to PF
-Fast sorting (None, Name, Size and Date is possible)
-Realtime sorting
-Soft Scrolling, in the Trumbs and the Pictures
-Copy/Move/Delete/Rename Files
-Show Filename/Filedate/Filesize/Filecomment/Proportions under Information
-3 Free selectable Textlines under the Trumbnails with the named propertys
-Display of Pictures, Auto Scaling to Screensize, full size, 1/2, 1/4 and 1/8
-Mousewheel support
-Saving of Trumbnails in one File to load the directory very fast next Time.
-Can show up to 97 Pictures at once.
-Can open pictures with more than 32 chars Filename lenght
-Rotating of pictures
-Saving of pictures in jpeg format
-Exif and Jpeg Comment support



Some Benchmarks:
Test System: A4000 CSPPC 68060RC60@60MHZ 604e@233 MHZ,CVision,OS3.9
Because PhotoFolio requires very long for sorting the Trumbnails the follow would be more slower,
but i compared only the loading of the Pictures.
Just one example for the 1st Benchmark PF would require 13:44 vs. 04:55.
PictureOverview require less than a second to sort 2260 pictures.
Trumbnailsize max.80x60 for every test.

1.Loading a Directory with 2260 jpeg Pictures
2.Loading a Directory with 144 ilbm/jpeg mix (OS3.9 Datatype/jpeg.library)
3.Loading a Directory with 752 png Pictures  (WarpPNG Datatype)
4.Loading a Directory with 435 gif Pictures    (OS3.9 Datatype)
5.Make Trumb File(s) of 2250 jpeg Pictures
6.Load Trumbnail File(s) with 2260 Pictures
PhotoFolio / PictureOverview
1. 11 Minutes 15 Seconds / 4 Minutes 55 Seconds
2.  1 Minute  11 Seconds / 35 Seconds
3. 10 Minutes 24 Seconds / 1 Minute  4 Seconds
4. 40 Minutes 42 Seconds / 4 Minutes 59 Seconds
5. 10 Minutes 52 Seconds / 5 Minutes 22 Seconds (incl. viewing)
6. 3 Minutes  50 Seconds / 42 Seconds

@ENDNODE


@NODE Requirements "Picture Overview: Requirements"


Operating System: >=OS3.1, OS3.5 or higher strongly recommend *1
Processor: >=68020
Ram: min. 3 MB Free additional requirement depends on the Pictures you load.
Graphics: Workbench Resolution of min. 640x512 with 15Bit, Cybergraphics
jpeg.library

*1 under OS3.1 the loading of non jpeg files over the datatypes takes much longer

There is no AGA support, cause nobody serious works with much Pictures but without a Graphicboard.
It seems to work with OS4.


@ENDNODE
