@NODE MainWindow "Picture Overview: Main Window"

Main Window:

+ Button: Adds a Directory to the Pfad list, you can doubleclick on the "-New-" Item in the list too.
++ Button: Adds a Directory including all subdirectorys.
X Button: Removes the selected Directory from the Pfad list.
Trumbnail Button: Makes a Overview of the selected Directory, you can doubleclick on a Item too.
4. Button: Load a Directory List
5. Button: Save a Directory List
? Button: Settings


Kontext Menu over a selected Entry:
 Rename - Renames the selected Directory
 Delete Directory    - Real delete!, not only the Entry of the List


@ENDNODE

@NODE Settings "Picture Overview: Settings"

Settings:

Trumbnail max x  - maximum horizontal size(pixel) of the Trumbs

Trumbnail max y  - maximum vertical size(pixel) of the Trumbs

Representation - Normal - display as many Trumbs as possible in a Line.
                 Same size - display each Trumb at least with max x width.
                 That means with "Normal" more vertical format images match in a Line than
		 with "Same size". But Same size looks more table like.
Scale Quality  - The scaling quality for the Datatypes. Normal and High is possible.

Sort By - Sort before the creation of the Trumbs. None, Filename, Date and Size are possible.
          If this setting was another while creating a Trumbnail file the viewing can be
          delayed. In this case you should create a new Trumbnail file.

Description 1:  Textline 1 under the Trumbnails. Filename, Date, Size, Dimensions and Comment are possible

Description 2:  Textline 2 under the Trumbnails. None, Filename, Date, Size, Dimensions and Comment are possible

Description 3:  Textline 3 under the Trumbnails. None, Filename, Date, Size, Dimensions and Comment are possible

Update after: After how many loaded Trumbs the Window is Updated. Updating is Fast no need for
              high numbers like with PhotoFolio. default is 4

Scroll Steps: The input.device give only a limited number of events in a period to the program.
              The scrolling with the Cusorkeys or with the Mousewheel would be slow.
              With this you can avoid that, it set the number of actions per event. Default is 12.

Scroll Delay: Thats for Amiga Models thats not yet exists or very overclocked ones on that the
              scrolling is too fast.

Textfont: The common Textfont that the program use.

Table Textfont: The Font that the Information-window use, that have the same size for each Letter to build a Table.

Initial Directory: Initial Dir after the program startup.

Jpeg Quality - Jpeg compression that is used to save the Trumbs File. Default: 86

User Command - To work on the Image with another Programm. Uses Arexx.
                    For Art Effect: 'ArtEffect' ; 'loadpic'
                    For Photogenics 'PHOTOGENICS.1' ; 'LOAD
Public Screen - For using on another Publicscreen than Workbench



If you change the Settings while other program windows are open it has no effect.
You can save but you have to restart the programm to use the new settings.


@ENDNODE

@NODE TrumbWin "Picture Overview: Trumbnail Window"

Trumnail Window:

Function:
Pictures are loaded via the jpeg.library and scaled, if the jpeg.library cant load the picture
its tryed over the Datatypes.

If a File named "Trumbs.po" exist in a Dir, the Trumbs are loaded from that. Thats faster.
If there are new images in the Dir against the Trumb File they are loaded additional
If pictures are deleted, they are not displayed.
From time to time you should make a new Trumb file if the directory is changed frequently.
This is not done automatic. Deleted images stay in the Trumbfile, too if they are not Displayed.
If you change the Trumbnail size in the settings the Trumbfile is invalid. Smaller would be 
loaded but are the Trumbs in the File bigger it loads all the Files again. In this case Save
the Trumbfile again.


You can Scroll with the Window gadget, with the cursorkey or with the Mousewheel.

While Loading:
Stop Button - Stops the Loading
Pause Button- Interrupt the loading/continue the loading

After Loading:
1. Button - Sort the Images by Name
2. Button - Sort the Images by Date
3. Button - Sort the Images by Size


Doubleclick on a Trumbnail shows the Picture.
Singleclick selects the Picture.

Kontext Menu:
Over a Trumbnail:
Information - Shows Information about the picture, if exist too JPEG Comment and Exif
Rename - Renames the picture
Copy - Copy the picture into another dir
Move - Move the picture from this dir into another dir
Delete - Delete the picture


Beside Trumbnails:
Select All - Select all Pictures
Select None - Unselect all Pictures
Copy selected - Copy all selected Pictures to another Dir
Move selected - Move all selected Pictures to another Dir
Delete selected - Delete all selected Pictures
Rename selected - Rename with Patterns Name001.jpg, NameTT.MM.JJJJ.jpg, NameTTMMJJJJ-HHMM.jpg 
                  Dates are taken from the Exif Header, if not exist from the Filedate.
		  If a File exists -1 to -99 is added to the Name
Save Trumbs - Save all loaded Trumbs in the File "Trumbs.po"
Delete Trumbs File - Delete the Trumbnail File, if exists 

Over the Window title bar:
Save Windowsize - Save the actual Windowsize. A cfg file has to be exist for that.



@ENDNODE

@NODE PicView "Picture Overview: Picture Viewing"


Picture viewing:

The Picture is scaled to a size that fit on the Screen, pictures smaller as the screen keeps untouched.


Kontext menu:
Match to Screen - The Default
Full - Shows the Picture in full size. If the picture is bigger than the Screen you can Scroll it
       with the Window Gadgets, Cursorkeys or the Mousewheel.
1/2 - Shows the Picture in halved size
1/4 - Shows the Picture in 1/4 size
1/8 - Shows the Picture in 1/8 size
Rotate +90° - Rotate the Picture 90° to the right
Rotate -90° - Rotate the Picture 90° to the left
Crop - Crops a selected area out of the Picture. You can select if you want use this function
       on the actual picture(for example 1/2) or on the full picture.
Gamma - Gamma correktiom -9 to +9 mean too -0.9/+0.9 or -90% to +90%
Save Jpeg  - Save the Picture like it is, if you scaled it or rotated it its saved with this.
[Extern] - If you Entered a User Command in the Settings this will be executed and the Picture
           for example forwarded to Photogenics. 


@ENDNODE

